{"TopicId":221000,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"VAB Camera Controls","CreatedByName":"ayork","CreatedById":88369,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-28T03:27:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ayork","CreatedById":88369,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-28T03:27:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease bring back KSP1 camera controls as an option.\u00A0 I play on a laptop and have no middle mouse button to click.\u00A0 Makes the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E a PIA.\u00A0 I should be able to play this on a laptop without having a mouse attached.\u00A0 Can\u0027t think of a valid reason the KSP1 controls should have been replaced.\u00A0 They were part of a very successful program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-28T07:09:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust give an option to rebind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-28T07:28:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not both?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002210f02n.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.29\u0022 height=\u0022261\u0022 width=\u0022419\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgflip.com/10f02n.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nControls-\u0026gt;\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, have everything (and I mean EVERYTHING) listed, and also the \u0022default\u0022 button could have a \u0022KSP1 Defaults\u0022 and \u0022KSP2 Defaults\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-28T07:57:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause people should move on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-28T08:09:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224343256\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221701156520\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not both?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.imgflip.com/10f02n.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002210f02n.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.29\u0022 height=\u0022261\u0022 width=\u0022419\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgflip.com/10f02n.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nControls-\u0026gt;\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, have everything (and I mean EVERYTHING) listed, and also the \u0022default\u0022 button could have a \u0022KSP1 Defaults\u0022 and \u0022KSP2 Defaults\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat \u0022KSP 1 Defaults\u0022? KSP 1 couldn\u0027t keep its control schemes straight between the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E lol, doing this would require the developers to not only create KSP 1 mappings but also have two of them, each of which conflicts with the horizontal or vertical modes. The entire point of the KSP 2 control scheme was to forego this mess. The solution is to just not think of the KSP 1 controls cause they were a problem the developers fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224343231\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221701142029\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002288369\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ayork\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, ayork said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI play on a laptop and have no middle mouse button to click.\u00A0 Makes the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E a PIA\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo address this point, I don\u0027t see why trackpad support has to involve what KSP 1 did. Why not just let the developers come up with their own solution that works with vertical and horizontal builds?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-28T08:10:29Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2023 08:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 28\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Bej Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}